{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"06fa9335-9c91-49a6-9391-801cbd7ce8d7","content":"The template has a few issues that should be addressed before publishing:\n\n**🔴 Likely Broken:**\n- **`choices` format is wrong** — Should be an array of objects, not a key-value object:\n  ```json\n  \"choices\": [\n    { \"choice\": \"net8.0\", \"description\": \".NET 8\" },\n    { \"choice\": \"net9.0\", \"description\": \".NET 9\" }\n  ]\n  ```\n\n**🟡 Recommended for NuGet:**\n- **Missing `$schema`** — Add `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for editor validation.\n- **Missing `description`** — Without it, `dotnet new list` shows a blank description. Poor UX.\n- **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Recommended when packaging templates for NuGet so multiple templates can be grouped.\n\n**✅ Looks Good:**\n- `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `author`, `sourceName` — all present and well-formed.\n- `classifications` and `tags` are correct.\n\n**Verdict:** Not ready — fix the `choices` array format (it may silently break the Framework parameter) and add a `description` at minimum.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4c21dc1e-5c31-4414-80bc-eb8ad872043a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I'll check against the .NET template engine schema requirements.\n\nIssues I can see:\n\n1. **Missing `$schema`** — Not strictly required, but highly recommended for validation and editor support. The standard value is `http://json.schemastore.org/template`.\n\n2. **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Recommended for NuGet package templates so multiple templates can be grouped together. Not strictly required though.\n\n3. **Missing `precedence`** — Useful when multiple versions of the same template exist. Not critical for a first publish.\n\n4. **Missing `preferNameDirectory`** — Optional but nice to have.\n\n\n5. **`defaultValue` references `net9.0`** — This works fine if you're targeting .NET 9.\n\n6. **Missing `description`** — Without it, `dotnet new list` will show an empty description column, which isn't ideal for discoverability.\n\n7. **The `Framework` symbol uses `datatype: \"choice\"` with `choices` as an object** — This needs to be an array instead, which is the correct format for the template engine. I need to verify the correct schema format against the official Microsoft documentation. The array format with objects containing `choice` and `description` properties is the documented standard, while the object-key format I initially considered isn't the proper specification and could cause compatibility issues.\n\nBeyond the critical `choices` format problem, there are several other gaps that would affect the template's usability: missing `$schema` for validation, no `description` field so users won't see what the template does in the CLI, and no `groupIdentity` which is recommended for package templates. The template might install, but the parameter handling could break and the user experience would suffer without proper metadata.","outputTokens":1408,"requestId":"A848:4CC71:74C98AF:8042D17:69F15815"},"id":"29e0daf5-3aa9-448e-b259-bead1d0f5b4e","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:00:33.876Z","parentId":"cb76d624-fb1f-4c2c-bb94-c740dd624e65"}
